post_cb({"4448691": {"Id": "4448691", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>ns2 will take priority as that is the namespace you are currently in. Why should the compiler think that you really meant ns1::f() ?</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-15T10:01:39.027", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-12-15T10:01:39.027", "ParentId": "4448598", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "290552"}, "4448737": {"Id": "4448737", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>This should work :</p>\n<pre><code>namespace ns1\n{\n    template &lt;class T&gt;\n    void f(T)\n    {\n        cout &lt;&lt; typeid(T).name() &lt;&lt; endl;\n    }\n};\n\n\n\nnamespace ns2\n{\n    using ns1::f;\n    void f(int)\n    {\n        cout &lt;&lt; \"int\" &lt;&lt; endl;\n    }\n\n    void test()\n    {\n        f(vector&lt;int&gt;()); // Error! \n        // Why not call ns1::f&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;(vector&lt;int&gt;()); ???\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-15T10:06:25.020", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2010-12-15T10:06:25.020", "ParentId": "4448598", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "541875"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_4448598_4448686_0": {"length": 45, "quality": 0.9, "section_id": 7083}, "so_4448598_4448686_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 7087}}, "n3337": {"so_4448598_4448686_0": {"length": 45, "quality": 0.9, "section_id": 6827}, "so_4448598_4448686_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 6831}}, "n4659": {"so_4448598_4448686_0": {"length": 30, "quality": 0.6, "section_id": 8584}, "so_4448598_4448686_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 8588}}}, "4448686": {"Id": "4448686", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>This has nothing to do with templates, but without name lookup.</p>\n<p>This is what the standard says in 3.4/1 (name lookup) :</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4448598_4448686_0\">Name lookup shall find an unambiguous\n  declaration for the name (see 10.2).\n  Name lookup may associate more than\n  one declaration with a name if it\n  finds the name to be a function name;\n  the declarations are said to form a\n  set of overloaded functions (13.1).\n  Overload resolution (13.3) takes place\n  after name lookup has succeeded. The\n  access rules (clause 11) are\n  considered only once name lookup and\n  function overload resolution (if\n  applicable) have succeeded.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And in 3.4.1 (unqualified name lookup) :</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4448598_4448686_1\"><strong>name lookup ends as soon as a declaration is found for the name</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In your case, <code>f</code> is an unqualified name. It is searched in the immediate scope, and in namespace <code>ns2</code> <strong>where a declaration is found</strong>. Name lookup ends here, and overload resolution comes into play : there is no overload in the candidate set which matches the argument type <code>std::vector&lt;int&gt;</code>, so the program is ill-formed.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-15T10:00:45.377", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2010-12-15T10:00:45.377", "ParentId": "4448598", "Score": "9", "OwnerUserId": "451980"}, "4448684": {"Id": "4448684", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Because when you're inside a namespace (ns2) it takes precedence over any others if names are unqualified.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-15T10:00:37.763", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2010-12-15T10:00:37.763", "ParentId": "4448598", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "476716"}, "4448598": {"ViewCount": "591", "Body": "<pre><code>namespace ns1\n{\n    template &lt;class T&gt;\n    void f(T)\n    {\n        cout &lt;&lt; typeid(T).name() &lt;&lt; endl;\n    }\n};\n\nusing namespace ns1;\n\nnamespace ns2\n{\n    void f(int)\n    {\n        cout &lt;&lt; \"int\" &lt;&lt; endl;\n    }\n\n    void test()\n    {\n        f(vector&lt;int&gt;()); // Error! \n        // Why not call ns1::f&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;(vector&lt;int&gt;()); ???\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "4448686", "Title": "Why does \"using namespace xxx\" not take effect on template functions?", "CreationDate": "2010-12-15T09:51:19.380", "Id": "4448598", "CommentCount": "0", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-15T10:06:25.020", "Score": "5", "OwnerUserId": "508343", "Tags": "<c++><namespaces>", "AnswerCount": "4"}});